                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00115A Pacific War/512: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-03-07T21:00:00-04:00"
                            >March 7, 1944—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>769. American Interests—Philippines. Effective March 1, 1944, the sum authorized
                    by Department’s 1979 of August 18, 1913,<note n="20" xml:id="d1037fn20">
                        <ref target="frus1943v03#pg_1030">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1943, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">iii</hi>, p. 1030</ref>.</note> for financial
                    assistance in the Philippines is hereby increased in compliance <pb facs="1034"
                        n="1022" xml:id="pg_1022"/> with the request in your 983 of February 17<note
                        n="21" xml:id="d1037fn21">Not printed; but for summary, see footnote 95,
                            <ref target="#pg_1015">p. 1015</ref>
                    </note> to an amount not exceeding $37,500 monthly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
